ions should be undone as a single atomic unit. ConditionalEditor.tsx:57-70 shows that a probability edit with multiple context conditions is submitted as a single mutation with one idempotencyKey. CptPanel.tsx:42-66 similarly submits one edit per cell interaction. Since each user 'submit' action produces exactly one API call with one payload, the natural undo granularity is one command per submit action. Partially undoing context conditions within a single edit would be confusing and could leave the CPT in an inconsistent state. The command pattern naturally supports this — each execute() call corresponds to one user action.\",\n      \"confidence\": 0.9,\n      \"evidence\": [\n        \"frontend/src/features/trading/ConditionalEditor.tsx:57-70\",\n        \"frontend/src/features/trading/CptPanel.tsx:42-66\",\n        \"frontend/src/features/assumptions/VariableRow.tsx:42-60\"\n      ],\n      \"uncertainty\": \"Whether there are scenarios where batch operations (e.g., clearing all assumptions via clearAll()) should be treated differently. clearAll() removes all assumptions at once — should undo restore all of them or just the last one?\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"assumption_checks\": [\n    {\n      \"assumption_id\": \"a1\",\n      \"verdict\": \"CORRECT\",\n      \"confidence\": 0.85,\n      \"impact\": \"Command pattern with execute/undo pairs is the right approach. Each command stores the previous state needed for undo (e.g., previous assumption for a variable). Full state snapshots would be wasteful since most commands affect a small portion of state.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"assumption_id\": \"a2\",\n      \"verdict\": \"CORRECT\",\n      \"confidence\": 0.9,\n      \"impact\": \"AssumptionProvider is already scoped to MarketDetail (lines 54-56). HistoryContext should wrap at the same level or just above it within MarketDetail. However, note that AssumptionProvider currently only wraps AssumptionPanel — HistoryContext needs to wrap more components (CptPanel, EventT